data.title: 2024: Celebrity News and Gossip
data.meta_description: Just Jared: The latest in entertainment news, photos, and celebrity gossip in tv, movies, music, pop culture and more!
data.text:
AMC just made a big renewal decision moments ago! So far this year, if you haven’t kept track, the fan fave network renewed a television show that has not been on the air since 2019. They also saved a TV show from cancellation at another network. Keep reading to see the renewals…

Superman is being arrested in these new photos from the set of the upcoming DC Universe film! David Corenswet was photographed in his full superhero suit on Wednedsay (June 26) in Cleveland, Ohio. Not only that: it looks like Frank Grillo‘s Rick Flag Sr. and María Gabriela de Faría‘s The Engineer were also on hand [...]

Chicago P.D. is heading back to our screens this fall! Season 12 of the One Chicago series is set to premiere later this year on NBC. The show follows the uniformed patrol officers and the Intelligence Unit of the 21st District of the Chicago Police Department as they go after the perpetrators of the city’s [...]

The debut trailer for A Good Girl’s Guide To Murder, led by Wednesday‘s Emma Myers, is finally here! Here’s the synopsis of the new series: Five years ago, schoolgirl Andie Bell was murdered by her boyfriend Sal Singh. Case closed. The police know he did it. Everyone in town knows he did it. But smart [...]

The members of SEVENTEEN are making history! The K-pop boy band attended a nomination ceremony on Wednesday (June 26) at UNESCO Headquarters in Paris, France, where they officially assumed their role as UNESCO’s first-ever Goodwill Ambassador for Youth. During the ceremony, SEVENTEEN spoke to importance of the strong companionship that brought them to where they [...]

Ayumi Hamasaki is back with a new theme song! The J-Pop icon, who is currently celebrating her 26th anniversary since her debut, has just released her latest single “Aurora.” The mid-tempo rock ballad serves as the official theme song for the 7th anniversary of the wildly popular game Azur Lane, which was first released in [...]

Kelly Bensimon has revealed why she called off her wedding to her husband-to-be, Scott Litner, four days before they were supposed to get married. The Real Housewives of New York City alum was supposed to get married on Saturday (June 29) in Boston, Mass. Keep reading to find out more…
